Logical Model: HIVDCareTreatment - Detailed Descriptions

Active as of 2025-07-08

Definitions for the HIVDCareTreatment logical model.

  • Key Elements Table
  • Differential Elements Table
  • Snapshot Elements Table

Guidance on how to interpret the contents of this table can be foundhere

0. HIVDCareTreatment
Definition

This tab describes the data that may be collected during care and treatment clinical visit for HIV workflow (HIV.D)

ShortHIV.D Care-Treatment
Control0..*
Is Modifierfalse
Logical ModelInstances of this logical model are not marked to be the target of a Reference
2. HIVDCareTreatment.reasonForVisit
Definition

Whether visit was scheduled or unscheduled, clinical only, or for ARV drug pick-up

ShortReason for visit
Control1..*
BindingThe codes SHALL be taken from Reason for visit ValueSet
(required to http://smart.who.int/hiv/ValueSet/HIV.D.DE1)
TypeCoding
Definitional CodesWHO SMART HIV Concepts CodeSystem HIV.D.DE1

Definition

Date client first enrols in HIV care at the facility. Begins when a person with a confirmed HIV diagnosis presents to a facility where HIV care is provided and a medical record, patient card, file or chart is opened for the first time. This could be at an HIV care/ART, MNCH or TB clinic.

146. HIVDCareTreatment.hivClinicalStage
Definition

WHO clinical stage of client based on signs and symptoms. WHO clinical staging is a way to categorize HIV disease severity based on new or recurrent clinical events. There are 4 WHO clinical stages that range from mild symptoms (WHO clinical stage 1) to severe symptoms (WHO clinical stage 4).

ShortHIV clinical stage
Control0..1
BindingThe codes SHALL be taken from HIV clinical stage ValueSet
(required to http://smart.who.int/hiv/ValueSet/HIV.D.DE186)
TypeCoding
Definitional CodesWHO SMART HIV Concepts CodeSystem HIV.D.DE186
